The paper deals with human action recognition using skeleton data, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of LSTM networks and feature fusion strategies suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of Kinect's skeletal data and tree-structure based traversal framework suggests a possible connection to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of multi-modal feature fusion suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
